        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Balt.</placeName>
                <date>6. April 1830</date>.</p>
            <p>Dear <addressee>Isaac</addressee></p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">I cannot permit <persName>W. Spencer</persName> to go on without
                saying<lb/> a word to you on the publication of your work. heretofore I
                attempted<lb/> to dissuade you from it. Tho I did not <sic>streinously</sic> urge it
                because<lb/> I saw that uncle favored your views. Do not feel so desirous<lb/> of
                making yourself known to the public. depend upon it I have no<lb/> other motive than
                your future happiness, and on this occasion we<lb/> differ most widely. Should you
                be successful in obtaining<lb/> subscribers sufficient to justify your commencement
                from that<lb/> moment I shall regard you with much feeling. You will have<lb/> In
                Christian populace upon. They will cry you down, and you have not the power to
                resist it. Can you believe that it can<lb/> have any effect in General? None
                whatever <sic>beleive</sic> me. Nay<lb/> now it requires much very much pruning
                &amp; correcting which<lb/> yourself will discover in a few years. Why not suspend
                it for a<lb/> future day. I feel great solicitude for you, much more than<lb/> I
                express. but depend upon it no one is more your friend than</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">
                <persName role="author">D. J.</persName>
            </p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p rend="align(center)">
                <addressee>Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
        </body>
